<p>
  When I was 14, I thought life would be better at 18.
</p>
<p>
  At 18, I thought it would be better at 22.
</p>
<p>
  At 22, I was already chasing 25.
</p>
<p>
  Now, I catch myself thinking life was better when I was 14.
</p>
<p>
  Maybe life was not better then. Maybe I was simply more present, before I
  learned to keep waiting for the next age to make me happy.
</p>
